mymap = leaflet() %>% addTiles()

election  = geojsonio::geojson_read("election.json", what = "sp")

#      
pal = colorFactor(c("#0D7440", "#2A88C5",  "#C10D0D"), c("", "",""))

#    
labs = lapply(seq(nrow(election@data)), function(i) {
  paste0( '<p><b>', election@data[i, ""]," : ",election@data[i, ""], '</b></p><p>', 
          "<b> : ", election@data[i, ""], '</b><p></p>', 
          " : ", election@data[i, ""],'</p><p>', 
          " : ", election@data[i, ""], '</p><p>',
          " : ", election@data[i, ""], '</p>') 
})

#   
election_gu = maptools::unionSpatialPolygons(election, election$)

poly2 = leaflet(election) %>%
  addTiles %>%
  addPolygons(
    #  
    fillColor = ~pal(), fillOpacity = 0.5,
    #  
    weight = 1, opacity = 1, color = "white", dashArray=3,
    # 
    label=lapply(labs, htmltools::HTML),
    # 
    highlightOptions = highlightOptions(
      color = "#00ff00", opacity = 1, weight = 2, fillOpacity = 1,
      bringToFront = T, sendToBack = T))%>%
  addLegend(pal = pal, values = ~, opacity = 0.7, title = NULL, position = "bottomright") %>%
  addPolylines(
    data=election_gu,
    weight = 1.5,
    opacity = 1,
    color = "black")

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
df1 = pd.read_csv('https://github.com/lhmlhm1111/Data_GongHak/raw/master/%EB%AA%A8%EB%8D%B8/12%2C16%EB%85%84%EB%8F%84_Training_Data_set_1.csv',encoding='UTF-8',sep=',')
x = '()'
k=15
for i in range(k):
    df1.loc[(df1[x] >= (df1[x].max()-df1[x].min())/k*i ) & (df1[x] <= (df1[x].max()-df1[x].min())/k*(i+1) ) ,x] = i+1

plt.rc('font', family='Malgun Gothic')
fig = plt.figure(figsize=[16,16])
ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax1 = sns.barplot(x,y='',data=df1.groupby(x)[''].mean().reset_index())
plt.title('-')
plt.show()
